    "body": "## Goal\nProvide the one piece of **new reference data** the Cycle-3 feature builder needs and the config section that the whole cycle reads. Create a static, deterministic **team \u2192 confederation** map (UEFA/CONMEBOL/CAF/AFC/CONCACAF/OFC) covering all 48 WC2026 teams plus common historical nations, and a small resolver that returns a FIFA-ranking-derived value when available and **degrades to confederation** when the ranking is stale (cnc8 data ends 2020-12-10) or absent. Ranking absence must never raise \u2014 it must fall back to the confederation covariate. This is a self-contained root slice with zero dependency on the assembler.\n\n## Context\nThis is the first task of Cycle 3 (Feature Assembly). The new `worldcup_playoff/features/` package does **not** exist yet, and there is **no** confederation map or FIFA-ranking loader anywhere in the repo (verified). The locked project decisions require **football-only** covariates \u2014 confederation is one of them.\n\nKey facts the implementer needs:\n- Team names everywhere are **crosswalk-normalized** canonical country names. `worldcup_playoff/data/crosswalk.py` exposes `normalize_team(name)`, `normalize_series(s)`, `CANONICAL_NAMES`, `is_known(name)`. Your `CONFEDERATION_MAP` keys **must match the canonical values** produced by the crosswalk exactly (e.g. `\"United States\"`, `\"South Korea\"`, `\"Ivory Coast\"`, `\"DR Congo\"`, `\"Cabo Verde\"`, `\"Turkey\"`, `\"Czech Republic\"`) so joins never miss. Resolve any input through `normalize_team` before lookup.\n- cnc8 `fifa_ranking-2020-12-10.csv` ends **2020-12-10** and exposes a `confederation` column \u2014 so confederation is a ready covariate regardless of ranking freshness. Per the locked decision, derive confederation from a **static map** (no network, no-key default).\n- Config convention (see `worldcup_playoff/config.py`): Pydantic `BaseModel` with `model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")`, `@field_validator` for bounds (mirror `EloConfig`/`PoissonConfig`), composed into `AppConfig`. The legacy `FeaturesConfig` (box-score column list) is **unrelated** \u2014 do **not** reuse it; add a **new** section.\n\n**Scope guard:** do NOT compute Elo/Dixon-Coles (Cycle 2, consume only), do NOT assemble per-match vectors (that is the sibling assembler task), do NOT train any model or add `[rf]` (Cycle 4), do NOT run backtests (Cycle 5). No socio-economic/market-value/GDP/odds data \u2014 football-only.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `confederation_of(\"Brazil\") == \"CONMEBOL\"`, `confederation_of(\"United States\") == \"CONCACAF\"`, `confederation_of(\"T\u00fcrkiye\") == \"UEFA\"` (alias resolves through the crosswalk), `confederation_of(\"Japan\") == \"AFC\"`, `confederation_of(\"New Zealand\") == \"OFC\"`.\n- [ ] Every WC2026 qualified nation maps to exactly one of the six confederations (parametrized \"no unmapped team\" test); unknown teams return `None` without raising.\n- [ ] `CONFEDERATIONS` is an immutable 6-tuple in a fixed, documented order; `CONFEDERATION_MAP` keys are all canonical (round-trip through `normalize_team` is identity).\n- [ ] `resolve_ranking(team, ranking=None, ...)` \u2192 `RankingResolution(value=None, confederation=<code>, used_fallback=True)`.\n- [ ] `resolve_ranking` with a fresh ranking dict and `as_of <= staleness_cutoff` \u2192 `used_fallback=False`, `value` populated; with `as_of > cutoff` or team absent \u2192 fallback path.\n- [ ] `FeatureBuildConfig` defaults load; invalid values (`form_window < 1`, `form_half_life_days <= 0`) raise `ValidationError`; `AppConfig().features_build` is a `FeatureBuildConfig`.\n- [ ] Module is I/O-free and network-free (no-key); deterministic.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- None \u2014 consumes the Cycle-1 `data/crosswalk.py` and `config.py` already merged on `main`.\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/features/__init__.py` \u2014 empty package marker here (the full `__all__` export surface is wired by the final exports task; leave a minimal docstring).\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/features/confederation.py`\n  - `CONFEDERATIONS: tuple[str, ...] = (\"UEFA\", \"CONMEBOL\", \"CAF\", \"AFC\", \"CONCACAF\", \"OFC\")`.\n  - `CONFEDERATION_MAP: dict[str, str]` \u2014 canonical-team-name \u2192 confederation; cover all 48 WC2026 teams + common historical nations. Keys MUST equal `crosswalk.CANONICAL_NAMES` values where applicable.\n  - `confederation_of(team: str) -> str | None` \u2014 `normalize_team` then dict lookup; `None` when unknown.\n  - Frozen dataclass `RankingResolution(value: float | None, confederation: str | None, used_fallback: bool)`.\n  - `resolve_ranking(team, ranking: Mapping[str, float] | None, as_of: str, staleness_cutoff: str, *, confed_map=CONFEDERATION_MAP) -> RankingResolution` \u2014 returns the ranking when present and not stale, else `used_fallback=True` with the confederation supplied.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/config.py` \u2014 add `class FeatureBuildConfig(BaseModel)` (`ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")`) with: `ranking_staleness_cutoff: str = \"2020-12-10\"`, `form_window: int = 5`, `form_half_life_days: float = 365.0`, `random_seed: int = 42`, `confederation_fallback: bool = True`. Add `@field_validator`s (`form_window >= 1`, `form_half_life_days > 0`) mirroring `PoissonConfig`. Register `features_build: FeatureBuildConfig = FeatureBuildConfig()` on `AppConfig` (additive \u2014 do not disturb `elo:`/`poisson:`/`features:`). Do NOT reuse the legacy `FeaturesConfig`.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_features_confederation.py` \u2014 BDD `test_when_..._then_...`; parametrize confederation lookups and the no-unmapped-team check; cover fallback paths and config validation. No network/I/O.\n- Conventions: `from __future__ import annotations`; frozen dataclass for the value object; `|` unions not `Optional`; `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`; mypy strict; ruff line-length 100.",
