    "title": "feat: time-aware recent-form, rest-days, and goal-difference helpers (no forward leakage)",
    "body": "## Goal\nBuild the pure, stateless helpers that compute the **strictly pre-match** time-dependent covariates \u2014 time-weighted recent form, rest days, and windowed goal difference \u2014 over a chronologically sorted match frame. Isolating these as pure functions makes the **no-forward-leakage** guarantee unit-testable in isolation, independent of Elo/Poisson. These are leaf functions consumed by the core assembler.\n\n## Context\nCycle 3 assembles per-match football-only covariates time-aware (a match's features may use only information available **strictly before** that match). The cleanest leakage guarantee is to anchor the whole builder to **one chronological sort** that is byte-identical to the Elo engine's sort, so each helper can read only rows with `index < before_idx`.\n\nKey facts:\n- `worldcup_playoff/data/elo.py` sorts internally by `[\"_d\", \"HOME_TEAM\", \"AWAY_TEAM\", \"HOME_GOALS\", \"AWAY_GOALS\"]` with `kind=\"stable\"`, `na_position=\"last\"`, then `reset_index(drop=True)` (where `_d = pd.to_datetime(df[\"DATE\"], errors=\"coerce\")`). Your `sort_chronological(df)` must **reproduce this exact key** so the sorted frame is positionally aligned 1:1 with `EloResult.match_diffs` (which the sibling assembler consumes).\n- Input frame schema (from `Martj42Loader.load_results()`): `DATE` (object ISO string), `HOME_TEAM`/`AWAY_TEAM` (normalized object), `HOME_GOALS`/`AWAY_GOALS` (nullable `Int64`, `<NA>` for unplayed incl. WC2026), `TOURNAMENT` (object), `NEUTRAL` (bool).\n- Reuse the existing decay primitive `decay_weight(age_days, half_life_days)` from `worldcup_playoff/simulation/poisson.py` (`0.5 ** (age/half_life)`) \u2014 do NOT redefine it.\n- `FeatureBuildConfig` (form_window, form_half_life_days, random_seed) comes from issue #7.\n\n**Scope guard:** pure compute only \u2014 no Elo/Poisson recompute (Cycle 2 consume), no per-match assembly (sibling task), no model/training (Cycle 4), no Monte Carlo (Cycle 5).\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `sort_chronological(df)` reproduces the Elo engine's sort key exactly (stable, `na_position=\"last\"`, reset index) \u2014 verified against a constructed frame.\n- [ ] `recent_form` for a team with a single prior 3-0 win returns the max decayed points-per-game; with no prior matches returns a defined neutral default (e.g. `0.0`) \u2014 pick one and assert it.\n- [ ] **No-leakage:** inserting a *later* match into the frame does not change `recent_form(before_idx=i)` for an earlier `i` (explicit test); helpers never read rows with `index >= before_idx`.\n- [ ] `rest_days` equals the exact day delta for a constructed two-match fixture; returns `None` on a team's first appearance.\n- [ ] A team appearing only as **away** still accumulates form/goal-difference (home/away symmetry test).\n- [ ] Unplayed prior fixtures (`<NA>` goals) are skipped by form/goal-difference but the documented rest-days convention is covered by a test.\n- [ ] Determinism: identical input frame \u2192 identical outputs across runs.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #7: feat: static confederation map + FIFA-ranking fallback resolver + [features_build] config (provides `FeatureBuildConfig`)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/features/timeaware.py`\n  - `sort_chronological(df) -> pd.DataFrame` \u2014 factor the sort-key column list as a shared module constant so it stays identical to `elo.py`.\n  - `recent_form(team, before_idx, sorted_df, *, window, half_life_days) -> float` \u2014 scan only rows `index < before_idx` where `team` appears (home or away), take the last `window` **played** matches, compute decay-weighted points-per-game (3/1/0 from the team's perspective) using `decay_weight` from `simulation.poisson`.\n  - `rest_days(team, before_idx, sorted_df) -> float | None` \u2014 days between the match date and the team's most recent prior **dated** match (`index < before_idx`); `None` if none. Document the convention for WC2026 future fixtures (rest-days uses the most recent dated prior match).\n  - `goal_difference(team, before_idx, sorted_df, *, window) -> float` \u2014 windowed net goal difference from the team's perspective over prior **played** matches.\n  - All four take `before_idx` and read only rows strictly before it \u2192 leakage structurally impossible.\n- **Modify:** none (these are leaf functions; exports are wired by the final exports task).\n- **Create:** `tests/test_features_timeaware.py` \u2014 BDD naming; in-memory DataFrames built by small local `_make_df` helpers; explicit no-leakage test (insert a later row, assert earlier outputs unchanged); home/away symmetry; rest-days delta and `None` edge case. No network/I/O.\n- Conventions: `from __future__ import annotations`; `|` unions; `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`; date arithmetic via `pd.to_datetime(..., errors=\"coerce\")`; mypy strict; ruff line-length 100.",
